<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 08 at 4:35PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Moore,
Scotland, southeastern Richmond and Hoke Counties through 530 PM
EDT...
At 434 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hamlet, or 7 miles east of Rockingham, moving northeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts to 45 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Southern Pines, Rockingham, Raeford, Pinehurst, Hamlet, Aberdeen,
Hoffman, Pinebluff, Dobbins Heights and Wagram.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
